Defendant in custody on another matter.
On count 1, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of seven (7) years.  That is four (4) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years.
On count 3, the defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total of three (3) years.  That is one (1) year initial confinement followed by two (2) years extended supervision, concurrent with the sentence imposed on count 1.  Execution of sentence is stayed and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) Pay restitution of $3,150.00 to Erik Johnson d/b/a Kiel Bait and Gun Store at 1148 6th Street, Kiel, WI;
2) Maintain fulltime employment or work search;
3) Pay court costs;
4) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) assessment, treatment and counseling as deemed appropriate by the Departments assessment process;
6) maintain absolute sobriety;
7) take all medications as prescribed and in prescribed doses;
8) spend six (6) months in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, consecutive to the sentence presently being served;
9) provide DNA sample and pay the surcharge.
Ineligible Voting Notice and Acknowledgement.
Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
